  <thing id="i5CAkmon" name="Akmon, Hammer of Purphoros" description="{b}Hammer of the Forge{/b}. This magic warhammer grants a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it. When you hit with an attack using it, the target takes an additional 3d10 fire damage.\n\n{b}Blessing of the Forge{/b}. If you aren&apos;t a worshiper of Purphoros, the hammer has 2 randomly determined minor detrimental properties. If you are a worshiper of Purphoros, you gain all the below piety benefits, so long as you have the piety required:\n{b}Piety 10+{/b}. The hammer has 1 randomly determined minor beneficial property.\n{b}Piety 25+{/b}. The hammer has 1 randomly determined major beneficial property.\n{b}Piety 50+{/b}. The hammer has another randomly determined major beneficial property.\nSee the Artifacts section in chapter 7 of the DMG for more information on randomly determined properties. Use the Artifact Properties tab to select the properties, and associate each property with this artifact once selected.\n\n{b}Reforged{/b}. While holding the hammer, you are resistant to fire damage and immune to exhaustion. Also, you are proficient with smith&apos;s tools and have advantage on all ability checks made using them.\n\n{b}Spells{/b}. While the hammer is on you, you can use an action to cast one of these spells (save DC 18): {i}animate objects{/i}, {i}heat metal{/i}, {i}fabricate{/i}, {i}magic weapon{/i}, {i}mending{/i}, {i}shatter{/i}. Once you use the hammer to cast a spell, that spell can&apos;t be cast from it again until the next dusk.\n\n{b}Destroying the Hammer{/b}. Consult your DM or the Mythic Odysseys of Theros sourcebook for details on destroying this artifact.\n\n\n{b}{i}Hero Lab Note{/i}{/b}. If your DM is allowing you to gain the Piety benefits of this weapon without worshipping its deity, add the &quot;Ignore Theros Artifact Restrictions&quot; adjustment to your character." compset="MagicWep">
