  <thing id="i5CDekella" name="Dekella, Bident of Thassa" description="{b}Bident of the Deep{/b}. This weapon functions as a trident that grants a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it. When you hit with an attack using the bident, the target takes an additional 2d10 cold damage.\n\n{b}Blessing of the Deep{/b}. If you aren&apos;t a worshiper of Thassa, the bident has 1 minor detrimental property and 1 major detrimental property, both randomly determined. If you are a worshiper of Thassa, you gain all the below piety benefits, so long as you have the piety required:\n{b}Piety 10+{/b}. You can breathe underwater, and you gain a swimming speed of 60 feet.\n{b}Piety 25+{/b}. The bident has 1 randomly determined minor beneficial property.\n{b}Piety 50+{/b}. The bident has 1 randomly determined major beneficial property.\nSee the Artifacts section in chapter 7 of the DMG for more information on randomly determined properties. Use the Artifact Properties tab to select the properties, and associate each property with this artifact once selected.\n\n{b}Command the Deep{/b}. You can use an action to change the condition of the sea within 1 mile of you, such as creating a violent, roiling storm or calming one. Regardless, the unnatural weather lasts for 1 hour before returning to normal. Once used, this property of the bident can&apos;t be used again until the next dusk.\nAdditionally, you can cast {i}dominate monster{/i} spell from the bident, but only on beasts and monstrosities with innate swimming speeds. Once used, this property of the bident can&apos;t be used again until the next dusk.\n\n{b}Aquatic Metamorphosis{/b}. You can cast {i}true polymorph{/i} (save DC 18) from the bident, but you must use it to turn the target creature into another creature with an innate swimming speed. Once used, this property of the bident can&apos;t be used again until the next dusk.\n\n\n{b}{i}Hero Lab Note{/i}{/b}. If your DM is allowing you to gain the Piety benefits of this weapon without worshipping its deity, add the &quot;Ignore Theros Artifact Restrictions&quot; adjustment to your character." compset="MagicWep">
