  <thing id="i5CEphixis" name="Ephixis, Bow of Nylea" description="{b}{/b}Bow of the Wild. This divine weapon includes a shortbow and a quiver with four arrows, each one representing a different season. You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this bow, and attacking at the weapon&apos;s long range imposes no disadvantage. Additionally, the bow scores a critical hit on a d20 roll of 19 or 20.\n\n{b}Blessing of the Wild{/b}. If you aren&apos;t a worshiper of Nylea, the bow has 1 randomly determined major detrimental property. If you are a worshiper of Nylea, you gain all the below piety benefits, so long as you have the piety required:\n{b}Piety 10+{/b}. The bow has 1 randomly determined minor beneficial property.\n{b}Piety 25+{/b}. The bow has 1 randomly determined major beneficial property.\nSee the Artifacts section in chapter 7 of the DMG for more information on randomly determined properties. Use the Artifact Properties tab to select the properties, and associate each property with this artifact once selected.\n\n{b}Arrows of the Seasons{/b}. The four arrows that accompany this bow cannot be fired from any other bow. Each arrow disappears immediately after it&apos;s used, and it reappears in the quiver at the next dusk. The arrows&apos; spell save DC is 18. Each arrow represents a season, and each has a unique property:\n{b}Spring.{/b} You can use an action to fire this arrow at a beast or a plant creature you can see within 320 feet of you. On a hit, the arrow deals no damage, and the target gains the benefits of the {i}awaken{/i} spell for 8 hours.\n{b}Summer.{/b} You can use an action to fire this arrow at an open space on the ground that you can see within 320 feet of you, requiring no attack roll. A Nyxborn lynx is summoned in that space (you can add this creature through the Encounter Builder). The lynx understands your verbal commands and obeys them as best it can, and it takes its turns immediately after yours. It fades away after 1 hour.\n{b}Autumn.{/b} You can use an action to fire this arrow at a space on the ground that you can see within 320 feet of you, requiring no attack roll. Doing so casts {i}wall of thorns{/i} in that spot.\n{b}Winter.{/b} You can use an action to fire this arrow at a space that you can see within 320 feet of you, requiring no attack roll. Doing so casts {i}ice storm{/i} in that spot.\n\n\n{b}{i}Hero Lab Note{/i}{/b}. If your DM is allowing you to gain the Piety benefits of this weapon without worshipping its deity, add the &quot;Ignore Theros Artifact Restrictions&quot; adjustment to your character." compset="MagicWep">
