  <thing id="i5CMastix" name="Mastix, Whip of Erebos" description="{b}Whip of the Dead{/b}. This magic whip grants a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it. When you hit with an attack using it, the target takes an additional 2d8 necrotic damage and you regain hit points equal to half the amount of necrotic damage dealt.\nAdditionally, when you make an attack with the whip on your turn, you can increase the range of the attack to 300 feet. This property of the weapon can&apos;t be used again until the next dusk.\n\n{b}Blessing of the Dead{/b}. If you aren&apos;t a worshiper of Erebos, the whip has 2 randomly determined major detrimental properties. If you are a worshiper of Erebos, you gain all the below piety benefits, so long as you have the piety required:\n{b}Piety 1+{/b}. The whip has 1 randomly determined minor detrimental property.\n{b}Piety 25+{/b}. The whip has 1 randomly determined major beneficial property.\n{b}Piety 50+{/b}. The whip has another randomly determined major beneficial property.\nSee the Artifacts section in chapter 7 of the DMG for more information on randomly determined properties. Use the Artifact Properties tab to select the properties, and associate each property with this artifact once selected.\n\n{b}Erebos&apos;s Claim{/b}. While carrying the whip, you can use an action to cast either {i}circle of death{/i} or {i}dominate monster{/i} (targeting only undead) from the whip (both with save DC 18). Once you have used the whip to cast a spell, that spell can&apos;t be cast from the whip again until the next dusk.\n\n{b}Destroying the Whip{/b}. Consult your DM or the Mythic Odysseys of Theros sourcebook for details on destroying this artifact.\n\n\n{b}{i}Hero Lab Note{/i}{/b}. If your DM is allowing you to gain the Piety benefits of this weapon without worshipping its deity, add the &quot;Ignore Theros Artifact Restrictions&quot; adjustment to your character." compset="MagicWep">
