  <thing id="io5CHlmGds" name="Helm of the Gods" description="While wearing this helm, you know whether there is a celestial or fiend within 30 feet of you, including its location, unless the creature is behind total cover.\nWhenever you complete a long rest while wearing the helm, you can pray to one of the gods listed in the table below, storing the corresponding spell in the helm. Any spell already stored there is replaced.\nThe helm has 3 charges, regaining 1d3 charges each dawn. To cast a spell from the helm (save DC 13), you must spend 1 charge.\n{back FFFFFF}\n{font Courier New}{b}God         Spell{/b}{back 010101}\nAthreos     protection from evil and good{back FFFFFF}\nEphara      sanctuary{back 010101}\nErebos      inflict wounds{back FFFFFF}\nHeliod      guiding bolt{back 010101}\nIroas       heroism{back FFFFFF}\nKarametra   goodberry{back 010101}\nKeranos     thunderous smite{back FFFFFF}\nKlothys     entangle{back 010101}\nKruphix     dissonant whispers{back FFFFFF}\nMogis       hellish rebuke{back 010101}\nNylea       faerie fire{back FFFFFF}\nPharika     lesser restoration{back 010101}\nPhenax      charm person{back FFFFFF}\nPurphoros   searing smite{back 010101}\nThassa      identify\n{revert}" compset="Wondrous">
