  <thing id="ip5CPtAqFrm" name="Potion of Aqueous Form" description="Drinking this potion transforms you into a pool of water. You return to your true form after 10 minutes or if you are incapacitated or die.\n\nYou&apos;re under the following effects while in this form:\n• {b}Liquid Movement{/b}. You have a swimming speed of 30 feet. You can move over or through other liquids. You can enter and occupy the space of another creature. You can rise up to your normal height, and you can pass through even Tiny openings. You extinguish nonmagical flames in any space you enter.\n• {b}Watery Resilience{/b}. You are resistant to nonmagical damage. You also have advantage on Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution saves.\n• {b}Limitations{/b}. You can&apos;t talk, attack, cast spells, or activate magic items. Any objects you were carrying or wearing meld into your new form and are not useable, though you continue to be affected by anything you&apos;re wearing, such as armor." compset="Potion">
