    </thing>
  <thing id="io5CFlyChrt" name="Flying Chariot" description="Both the riders of the chariot and the creatures pulling it gain a +1 bonus to their AC. It can fly if one or more flying creatures is pulling it.\n\n{b}Chariots{/b}. Chariots and the creatures pulling them function like controlled mounts (see Mounted Combat in Chapter 9 of the PHB), but with these differences:\n• Mounting or dismounting a chariot costs you 5 feet of movement instead of half your speed.\n• The chariot grants you half cover while you&apos;re mounted on it.\n• The chariot&apos;s speed equals the speed of the slowest creature pulling it.\n• If multiple creatures are pulling the chariot, they all act on the same initiative, and they must take the same action on their turn." compset="Wondrous">
